{
  "abstract": "A true breeding, spontaneous, prostrate mutant was found in the population of pigeonpea [Cajanus cajan (L.) Millsp.) germplasm accession 1CP 102, The mutant grows horizontally on the ground. Inheritance studies conducted in F1, F2 and testcross generations of two crosses indicated that this trait is controlled by a single recessive gene.",
